<p>
	Strained, sprained and tired muscles can occur in people of all ages. This special natural muscle rub has been designed for anyone needlessly suffering from persistent muscle stiffness whether caused through regular exercise, sports participation, walking, gardening or work etc. This therapeutic natural muscle rub is&nbsp;reputed to be anti-inflammatory and is ideal for everyday use or as a treatment before and after sport or exercise. Our special beeswax provides a protective layer over the skin allowing the essential oils to penetrate deep into the body. Made with a blend of natural ingredients reputed to rehabilitate sore muscles, reduce muscle pain, relieve tired muscles and prevent muscle cramps.</p>
<p>
	Directions: massage a small amount of ointment directly onto the areas requiring treatment approximately four times per day or rub well into muscles before and after sport or exercise. The ointment will form a very slightly greasy layer on top of the skin while the essential oils penetrate and get to work in the muscles.</p>
<p>
	Our Avena S.S. ointment only contains lovely natural goodness! It has NO- parabens, sodium laureth sulfate (SLS), sodium lauryl ether sulfate (SLES), alcohol, synthetic oils, artificial colours or preservatives, animal additives or chemical additives. It has not been tested on animals and we don&rsquo;t buy ingredients from companies that test on animals or ever have.</p>
<p>
	Ingredients- sunflower oil (Helianthus annuus), beeswax (Cera alba), sweet almond oil (Prunus amygdalus dulcis), rosemary essential oil (Rosmarinus officinalis), thyme essential oil (Thymus vulgaris), lavender essential oil (Lavandula angustifolia) and vitamin E oil (Tocopherol). Please note that our Sprains &amp; Strains ointment does contain nut oils and is for external use only. Please consult your doctor before using products containing essential oils if you are currently suffering from any medical conditions, are pregnant or breastfeeding. &copy; Please do not copy text - Avena product description - AVOINT2.&nbsp;</p>
